Date: 1997-10-21

Title: The Second-Order Equation from the (1/2,0)+ (0,1/2) Representation of

the Poincare GroupComments: 6pp. ReVTeX file

Journal-ref: Int. J. Theor. Phys., v. 37, No. 7 (1998) 1909-1914

On the basis of the first principles we derive the Barut-Wilson-Fushchichsecond-order equation in the (1/2,0)+(0,1/2) representation. Then we discussthe possibility of the description of various mass and spin states in such aframework.